      <ul>      
        <li><a href="http://www.rabbitmq.com/documentation.html">RabbitMQ documentation and Getting Started Guide</a> </li>
        <li><a href="http://www.slideshare.net/somic/introduction-to-amqp-messaging-with-rabbitmq/">Introduction to AMQP Messaging with RabbitMQ</a></li>
        <li>Films of presentations we made at the RabbitMQ Tech Talk at Google London on Tuesday 12th May 2009:
	<ul>
      <li>Alexis on <a href="http://skillsmatter.com/podcast/erlang/alexis-richardson-introduction-to-rabbitmq">RabbitMQ's internal architecture</a></li>
      <li>Mike Bridgen on <a href="http://skillsmatter.com/podcast/erlang/mike-bridgen-application-of-rabbitmq">one application of RabbitMQ at the BBC</a></li>
      <li>Tony on <a href="http://skillsmatter.com/podcast/erlang/rabbitmq-internal-architecture-tony-garnock-jones">RabbitMQ's internal architecture</a></li>
      </ul>
	</li>	
	<li><a href="/resources/RabbitMQ_Oxford_Geek_Night.pdf">Messaging v Databases</a>, slides from presentataion given by Alexis at Oxford Geek Night, May 2009.</li>
        <li><a href="http://blogs.digitar.com/jjww/2009/01/rabbits-and-warrens/">Rabbits and Warrens, an introduction to messaging</a></li>
        <li>Whether you use .NET or not, <a href="http://www.rabbitmq.com/releases/rabbitmq-dotnet-client/v1.5.3/rabbitmq-dotnet-client-1.5.3-user-guide.pdf">section 3 of this user guide</a> describes common messaging patterns</li>
        <li><a href="http://es.cohesiveft.com/site/rabbitmq">Run RabbitMQ right now on EC2 or a VM</a> and <a href="http://delicious.com/alexisrichardson/rabbitmq+cloud+usecase">some use cases for the cloud</a></li>
        <li><a href="http://somic.org/2008/11/11/using-rabbitmq-beyond-queueing/">Using RabbitMQ Beyond Queueing</a></li>
        <li><a href="http://enthusiasm.cozy.org/archives/2009/02/listening-to-the-system">Some more complex use cases for RabbitMQ</a></li>
        <li><a href="http://del.icio.us/alexisrichardson/rabbitmq">Del.icio.us links</a></li>
      </ul>
      <h3 id="examples">Real-world examples</h3>
     <ul>
        <li>More on use of RabbitMQ at the BBC in <a href="http://www.lshift.net/blog/2009/05/08/untangling-the-bbcs-data-feeds">Mike's blog on BBC 'Feedshub'</a></li>
	<li>Overview of how NASA use RabbitMQ in their <a href="http://nebula.nasa.gov/services"> NEBULA Cloud Computing Platform</a></li>
	<li>We'll add more usecases to this list of examples, in the meantime there's a list of <a href="http://delicious.com/alexisrichardson/rabbitmq+usecase">use cases stored on Del.icio.us</a></li>
      </ul>
      
      <h3 id="clients">Specific configurations</h3>
      <ul>
