        <li>.NET <a href="http://www.rabbitmq.com/dotnet.html">overview</a> and <a href="http://www.rabbitmq.com/releases/rabbitmq-dotnet-client/v1.5.3/rabbitmq-dotnet-client-1.5.3-user-guide.pdf">.NET Client Library User Guide</a></li>
        <li><a href="http://code.google.com/p/php-amqplib/">PHP client</a></li> 
        <li><a href="http://hopper.squarespace.com/blog/2008/3/24/as3-amqp-client-first-cut.html">AS3</a>, <a href="http://geekrelief.wordpress.com/2008/12/15/hxamqp-amqp-with-haxe/">Haxe</a> and <a href="http://flexonrails.net/?p=106">Flex</a></li>     
        <li>JSON/HTTP, our experimental project, <a href="http://www.rabbitmq.com/download.html#rabbitmq-http">rabbitmq-http2</a> and <a href="http://hg.rabbitmq.com/rabbitmq-http2/file/default/README">code</a></li>
        <li><a href="http://markmail.org/message/2phdwvrvwc57ya5m">C Client</a> and also an experimental <a href="http://hg.rabbitmq.com/rabbitmq-c/">RabbitMQ-C</a></li>
        <li><a href="http://www.lshift.net/blog/2008/02/02/how-to-run-rabbitmqs-experimental-stomp-adapter">Stomp</a></li>
        <li><a href="http://hg.rabbitmq.com/rabbitmq-xmpp/raw-file/default/doc/index.html">XMPP adaptor</a>.  See also "<a href="https://dev.rabbitmq.com/wiki/RabbiterFederation">rabbiter</a>", an experiment in
decentralised microblogging</li>
        <li><a href="http://scala-tools.org/mvnsites/liftweb/lift-amqp/scaladocs/index.html">Scala/Lift</a></li>
